## 4 Things That Will Get You Approved (or Rejected)

Malaysian financiers (including us) usually look at these four pillars:

1.  **Business Age:** Banks love companies with 3+ years of history. Alternative lenders like Ing Heng Credit are often happy to work with startups (1-2 years) if the business model is solid.
2.  **Bank Statements:** We look at your average daily balance and monthly turnover. We want to see that you have enough "extra" cash to comfortably pay the installment.
3.  **Credit History (CCRIS/CTOS):** A few late payments won't always kill your deal with an alternative lender, but major defaults or legal suits will.
4.  **Equipment Type:** Brand-new equipment from a reputable brand (Caterpillar, Hino, Komatsu) is much easier to finance than 15-year-old, "no-name" machinery.

